Jshih 5 add donor page

commit.message:
Added permissions to routes:
- volunteers can't access donor pages (progress)
- donor pages can't access volunteer pages
- guests can't access pages that require registration
- pages without route handling cannot be accessed
- all of the above are handled with a 404 page not found
User first name / type display moved from donor-pages.script.js to the ejs templates themselves
Removed pug/html files for progress and event views since we're using ejs
routes.js - Added extensions (pug vs ejs) to render templates
index.js - added ejs as a view engine
Added ejs to package.json, will need this for templating HTML
Added routes for progress and event, did not add auth for it yet
Renamed haiti.html to event.html to be more generic, added event.pug to import event.html
Changed redirection path for haiti from html file to progress/haiti
Can't directly render HTML files, so created progress.pug to import progress.html
index.js - added js/views/donor-pages as static folder for progress page; also added warning about using multiple static folders
moved donor-pages so that html files are in views (for dynamic rendering) and other files are in public (static files)
navbar - added progress button for donors
Moved glitch files to donor-pages folder
Merge remote-tracking branch 'donor-pages/glitch' into jshih-5-add-donor-page
Added SQL script to add new user and grant permissions to ReAction DB
index.js - Added express-session options to remove node warnings
Added comments to Makefile about making new user and granting privileges
Added Makefile to run npm + other commands in bundles
package.json mods - added clean to remove node_modules, models now removes and rebuilds models, watch looks for css files

commit.message: Removed extraneous buttons from navbar
Added dashboard template

Modified routes.js:
- added dashboard routes for when user logs in / registers
- used sessions with dashboard so that it displays the user's name / type
- added functions to check authorization before certain routes so that if a user is logged in or logged out, they are redirected to another route
index.js - added express-session to middleware
Removed cookie-parser from package.json b/c express-session documentation says we don't need it, in fact it may cause issues
